[2]
Date: 21 Nov 2002
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Food Safety and Inspection Service Recall (edited)
<http://www.fsis.usda.gov/OA/recalls/rnrfiles/rnr098-2002.htm>

Recall Notification Report 098-2002 Expanded, 21 Nov 2002
---------------------------------------------------------------
Product(s) Recalled: Fresh and Frozen Ready-To-Eat Turkey and Chicken Products
In response to an ongoing food safety investigation, FSIS collected
microbiological investigative sample on 14 Nov 2002, that returned positive
results for _Listeria monocytogenes_ on 20 Nov 2002. Based on this positive
the firm has voluntarily expanded the recall 098-2002 to include turkey and
chicken products produced between 29 May 2002 and 2 Nov 2002. The sample is
being further analyzed to determine whether or not it matches the outbreak
strain.
Production Dates/Identifying Codes:
Produced between 29 May 2002 and 2 Nov 2002. Each product label bears the
establishment number "P-4340" inside the USDA mark of inspection. [The long
list of the products under recall can be found at the above web site. -
Mod. LL]
Problem/Reason for Recall:
The products may be contaminated with _Listeria monocytogenes_.
How/When Discovered:
On 3 Oct 2002, FSIS collected samples from retail as part of an ongoing
food safety investigation of illnesses in the Northeastern United States.
An intact sample was reported positive for _L. monocytogenes_ by the FSIS
Outbreaks Laboratory. The positive results strongly suggest that the
recalled products may be linked to the source of the widespread illnesses
in the Northeastern US. Based on this information firm has voluntarily
initiated the recall and suspended its operations.
In response to an on-going food safety investigation, FSIS collected
microbiological investigative sample on 14 Nov 2002, that returned positive
results for _L. monocytogenes_ on 20 Nov 2002. Based on this positive the
firm has voluntarily expanded the recall 098-2002 to include turkey and
chicken products produced between 29 May 2002 and 2 Nov 2002. The sample is
being further analyzed to determine whether or not it matches the outbreak
strain.
Establishment: 4340 P
Jack Lambersky Poultry Inc.
Quantity Recalled: Approximately 4.2 million pounds (This includes the
200 000 pounds from 2 Nov 2002 recall)
Consumer Inquiries: 1-800-535-4555
Web Site: <http://www.fsis.usda.gov/oa/recalls/rec_intr.htm>
